9

; 
bst
) indistinctly demarcated from procoxal cavities (

Fig. 
9

; 
pcc
) by diffused bisinuate carina; median part of sternum with rudimentary prosternal intercoxal process developed as indistinct protuberance with rounded apex; procoxal sockets (

Fig. 
9

; 
pcs
) nearly closed by narrow postero-lateral lobes of prosternum; hypomera (

Fig. 
9

; 
hy
